The paper deals with graphical user interface layouts, which are typically studied in the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. The use of OR-constraints and the proposed solving technique involve optimization and search algorithms, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper also discusses the use of programming languages and constraints, which are relevant to programming languages (cs.PL).
